# Docs and testing — mandatory every slice

**Do not hand off feature work until user-facing docs and testing artefacts match the code.** This is as mandatory as audit footers and push-and-test.

## When this applies

Any slice that adds or changes user-visible behaviour, routes, processes, windows, seeds, or printable/send flows.

## Required updates (complete all that apply)

### How-to guides (in-app)

| Change type | Update |
|-------------|--------|
| New/changed workspace behaviour | Section(s) in `web/src/lib/help/articles/` (e.g. `clients-locations.ts`, `document-templates.ts`) |
| New module or setup step | `web/src/lib/help/articles/module-setup-guides.ts` |
| New route | `web/src/lib/help/page-guides.ts` if needed; run `npm run page-guides:check` |

Set `lastUpdated` on touched help articles.

### Testing documentation (`docs/testing/`)

| Change type | Update |
|-------------|--------|
| Happy-path step | [HAPPY-PATH-E2E-MATRIX.md](../docs/testing/HAPPY-PATH-E2E-MATRIX.md) — HP row + FUNC catalogue row |
| Executable smoke | [TEST-RUNBOOKS.md](../docs/testing/TEST-RUNBOOKS.md) — steps under the matching TEST ID |
| Module UAT | Relevant `docs/testing/uat/UAT-*.md` pack (scenario row + result when tested) |
| New process in `access/catalog.ts` | Run `npm run uat:inventory`; update [UAT-15-processes.md](../docs/testing/uat/UAT-15-processes.md) |
| New window | Run `npm run uat:inventory`; add scenario to module pack |
| Defects found | [ISSUE-LOG-TEMPLATE.md](../docs/testing/ISSUE-LOG-TEMPLATE.md) |

### Other docs (when applicable)

- [docs/core/SYSTEM-FUNCTION-GUIDE.md](../docs/core/SYSTEM-FUNCTION-GUIDE.md) — function outcomes (reviewers)
- [docs/core/WINDOWS-AND-TABS.md](../docs/core/WINDOWS-AND-TABS.md) — routes, window keys, tabs (see `core-reference-docs.mdc`)
- [docs/DATABASE-CHANGES.md](../docs/DATABASE-CHANGES.md) — new tables/columns
- [dev-core/AGENT-PLAYBOOK.md](../dev-core/AGENT-PLAYBOOK.md) handoff checklist — already references guides; follow it
- [docs/BUILD-PROGRESS.md](../docs/BUILD-PROGRESS.md) — **What you can test** for the slice

## Order (with push-and-test)

1. Implement code
2. **Update docs** (this rule)
3. Tier 1 verify (`build`, `page-guides:check`)
4. Tier 2 browser smoke
5. Bugbot
6. Commit **code + docs together**
7. Push
8. Handoff **Verification** block must list doc files updated

## Never

- Ship UI/process features with stale help articles or missing TEST/UAT rows.
- Say "docs can be updated later."
- Hand off without naming which help articles and testing files were touched.

## Exceptions

- Pure refactors with no user-visible or test-surface change.
- User explicitly says docs-only or no-docs for that turn.
